ipMRouteStdMIB.name: ipMRouteStdMIB
ipMRouteStdMIB.contactinfo: Dave Thaler Microsoft Corporation One Microsoft Way Redmond, WA 98052-6399 US Phone: +1 425 703 8835 EMail: dthaler@microsoft.com
ipMRouteStdMIB.description: The MIB module for management of IP Multicast routing, but independent of the specific multicast routing protocol in use.

LanguageTag.name: LanguageTag
LanguageTag.description: An RFC 1766-style language tag, with all alphabetic characters converted to lowercase. This restriction is intended to make the lexical ordering imposed by SNMP useful when applied to language tags. Note that it is theoretically possible for a valid language tag to exceed the allowed length of this syntax, and thus be impossible to represent with this syntax. Sampling of language tags in current use on the Internet suggests that this limit does not pose a serious problem in practice.

ipMRouteEnable.name: ipMRouteEnable
ipMRouteEnable.description: The enabled status of IP Multicast routing on this router.

ipMRouteEntryCount.name: ipMRouteEntryCount
ipMRouteEntryCount.description: The number of rows in the ipMRouteTable. This can be used to monitor the multicast routing table size.

ipMRouteTable.name: ipMRouteTable
ipMRouteTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information for IP datagrams sent by particular sources to the IP multicast groups known to this router.

ipMRouteEntry.name: ipMRouteEntry
ipMRouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for IP datagrams from a particular source and addressed to a particular IP multicast group address. Discontinuities in counters in this entry can be detected by observing the value of ipMRouteUpTime.

ipMRouteGroup.name: ipMRouteGroup
ipMRouteGroup.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

ipMRouteSource.name: ipMRouteSource
ipMRouteSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteSourceMask identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

ipMRouteSourceMask.name: ipMRouteSourceMask
ipMRouteSourceMask.description: The network mask which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteSource identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

ipMRouteUpstreamNeighbor.name: ipMRouteUpstreamNeighbor
ipMRouteUpstreamNeighbor.description: The address of the upstream neighbor (e.g., RPF neighbor) from which IP datagrams from these sources to this multicast address are received, or 0.0.0.0 if the upstream neighbor is unknown (e.g., in CBT).

ipMRouteInIfIndex.name: ipMRouteInIfIndex
ipMRouteInIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface on which IP datagrams sent by these sources to this multicast address are received. A value of 0 indicates that datagrams are not subject to an incoming interface check, but may be accepted on multiple interfaces (e.g., in CBT).

ipMRouteUpTime.name: ipMRouteUpTime
ipMRouteUpTime.description: The time since the multicast routing information represented by this entry was learned by the router.

ipMRouteExpiryTime.name: ipMRouteExpiryTime
ipMRouteExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. The value 0 indicates that the entry is not subject to aging.

ipMRoutePkts.name: ipMRoutePkts
ipMRoutePkts.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address.

ipMRouteDifferentInIfPackets.name: ipMRouteDifferentInIfPackets
ipMRouteDifferentInIfPackets.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, which were dropped because they were not received on the interface indicated by ipMRouteInIfIndex. Packets which are not subject to an incoming interface check (e.g., using CBT) are not counted.

ipMRouteOctets.name: ipMRouteOctets
ipMRouteOctets.description: The number of octets contained in IP datagrams which were received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, and which were forwarded by this router.

ipMRouteProtocol.name: ipMRouteProtocol
ipMRouteProtocol.description: The multicast routing protocol via which this multicast forwarding entry was learned.

ipMRouteRtProto.name: ipMRouteRtProto
ipMRouteRtProto.description: The routing mechanism via which the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry was learned. Inclusion of values for routing protocols is not intended to imply that those protocols need be supported.

ipMRouteRtAddress.name: ipMRouteRtAddress
ipMRouteRtAddress.description: The address portion of the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry.

ipMRouteRtMask.name: ipMRouteRtMask
ipMRouteRtMask.description: The mask associated with the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry.

ipMRouteRtType.name: ipMRouteRtType
ipMRouteRtType.description: The reason the given route was placed in the (logical) multicast Routing Information Base (RIB). A value of unicast means that the route would normally be placed only in the unicast RIB, but was placed in the multicast RIB (instead or in addition) due to local configuration, such as when running PIM over RIP. A value of multicast means that the route was explicitly added to the multicast RIB by the routing protocol, such as DVMRP or Multiprotocol BGP.

ipMRouteHCOctets.name: ipMRouteHCOctets
ipMRouteHCOctets.description: The number of octets contained in IP datagrams which were received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, and which were forwarded by this router. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteOctets.

ipMRouteNextHopTable.name: ipMRouteNextHopTable
ipMRouteNextHopTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on the next- hops on outgoing interfaces for routing IP multicast datagrams. Each entry is one of a list of next-hops on outgoing interfaces for particular sources sending to a particular multicast group address.

ipMRouteNextHopEntry.name: ipMRouteNextHopEntry
ipMRouteNextHopEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the list of next-hops on outgoing interfaces to which IP multicast datagrams from particular sources to a IP multicast group address are routed. Discontinuities in counters in this entry can be detected by observing the value of ipMRouteUpTime.

ipMRouteNextHopGroup.name: ipMRouteNextHopGroup
ipMRouteNextHopGroup.description: The IP multicast group for which this entry specifies a next-hop on an outgoing interface.

ipMRouteNextHopSource.name: ipMRouteNextHopSource
ipMRouteNextHopSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteNextHopSourceMask identifies the sources for which this entry specifies a next-hop on an outgoing interface.

ipMRouteNextHopSourceMask.name: ipMRouteNextHopSourceMask
ipMRouteNextHopSourceMask.description: The network mask which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteNextHopSource identifies the sources for which this entry specifies a next-hop on an outgoing interface.

ipMRouteNextHopIfIndex.name: ipMRouteNextHopIfIndex
ipMRouteNextHopIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for the outgoing interface for this next-hop.

ipMRouteNextHopAddress.name: ipMRouteNextHopAddress
ipMRouteNextHopAddress.description: The address of the next-hop specific to this entry. For most interfaces, this is identical to ipMRouteNextHopGroup. NBMA interfaces, however, may have multiple next-hop addresses out a single outgoing interface.

ipMRouteNextHopState.name: ipMRouteNextHopState
ipMRouteNextHopState.description: An indication of whether the outgoing interface and next- hop represented by this entry is currently being used to forward IP datagrams. The value 'forwarding' indicates it is currently being used; the value 'pruned' indicates it is not.

ipMRouteNextHopUpTime.name: ipMRouteNextHopUpTime
ipMRouteNextHopUpTime.description: The time since the multicast routing information represented by this entry was learned by the router.

ipMRouteNextHopExpiryTime.name: ipMRouteNextHopExpiryTime
ipMRouteNextHopExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. If ipMRouteNextHopState is pruned(1), the remaining time until the prune expires and the state reverts to forwarding(2). Otherwise, the remaining time until this entry is removed from the table. The time remaining may be copied from ipMRouteExpiryTime if the protocol in use for this entry does not specify next-hop timers. The value 0 indicates that the entry is not subject to aging.

ipMRouteNextHopClosestMemberHops.name: ipMRouteNextHopClosestMemberHops
ipMRouteNextHopClosestMemberHops.description: The minimum number of hops between this router and any member of this IP multicast group reached via this next-hop on this outgoing interface. Any IP multicast datagrams for the group which have a TTL less than this number of hops will not be forwarded to this next-hop.

ipMRouteNextHopProtocol.name: ipMRouteNextHopProtocol
ipMRouteNextHopProtocol.description: The routing mechanism via which this next-hop was learned.

ipMRouteNextHopPkts.name: ipMRouteNextHopPkts
ipMRouteNextHopPkts.description: The number of packets which have been forwarded using this route.

ipMRouteInterfaceTable.name: ipMRouteInterfaceTable
ipMRouteInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information specific to interfaces.

ipMRouteInterfaceEntry.name: ipMRouteInterfaceEntry
ipMRouteInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for a particular interface.

ipMRouteInterfaceIfIndex.name: ipMRouteInterfaceIfIndex
ipMRouteInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which this entry contains information.

ipMRouteInterfaceTtl.name: ipMRouteInterfaceTtl
ipMRouteInterfaceTtl.description: The datagram TTL threshold for the interface. Any IP multicast datagrams with a TTL less than this threshold will not be forwarded out the interface. The default value of 0 means all multicast packets are forwarded out the interface.

ipMRouteInterfaceProtocol.name: ipMRouteInterfaceProtocol
ipMRouteInterfaceProtocol.description: The routing protocol running on this interface.

ipMRouteInterfaceRateLimit.name: ipMRouteInterfaceRateLimit
ipMRouteInterfaceRateLimit.description: The rate-limit, in kilobits per second, of forwarded multicast traffic on the interface. A rate-limit of 0 indicates that no rate limiting is done.

ipMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets.name: ipMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets
ipMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface, including framing characters. This object is similar to ifInOctets in the Interfaces MIB, except that only multicast packets are counted.

ipMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets.name: ipMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets
ipMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface.

ipMRouteInterfaceHCInMcastOctets.name: ipMRouteInterfaceHCInMcastOctets
ipMRouteInterfaceHCInMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets. It is similar to ifHCInOctets in the Interfaces MIB, except that only multicast packets are counted.

ipMRouteInterfaceHCOutMcastOctets.name: ipMRouteInterfaceHCOutMcastOctets
ipMRouteInterfaceHCOutMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets.

ipMRouteBoundaryTable.name: ipMRouteBoundaryTable
ipMRouteBoundaryTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's scoped multicast address boundaries.

ipMRouteBoundaryEntry.name: ipMRouteBoundaryEntry
ipMRouteBoundaryEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the ipMRouteBoundaryTable representing a scoped boundary.

ipMRouteBoundaryIfIndex.name: ipMRouteBoundaryIfIndex
ipMRouteBoundaryIfIndex.description: The IfIndex value for the interface to which this boundary applies. Packets with a destination address in the associated address/mask range will not be forwarded out this interface.

ipMRouteBoundaryAddress.name: ipMRouteBoundaryAddress
ipMRouteBoundaryAddress.description: The group address which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteBoundaryAddressMask identifies the group range for which the scoped boundary exists. Scoped addresses must come from the range 239.x.x.x as specified in RFC 2365.

ipMRouteBoundaryAddressMask.name: ipMRouteBoundaryAddressMask
ipMRouteBoundaryAddressMask.description: The group address mask which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteBoundaryAddress identifies the group range for which the scoped boundary exists.

ipMRouteBoundaryStatus.name: ipMRouteBoundaryStatus
ipMRouteBoundaryStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

ipMRouteScopeNameTable.name: ipMRouteScopeNameTable
ipMRouteScopeNameTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the multicast scope names.

ipMRouteScopeNameEntry.name: ipMRouteScopeNameEntry
ipMRouteScopeNameEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the ipMRouteScopeNameTable representing a multicast scope name.

ipMRouteScopeNameAddress.name: ipMRouteScopeNameAddress
ipMRouteScopeNameAddress.description: The group address which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteScopeNameAddressMask identifies the group range associated with the multicast scope. Scoped addresses must come from the range 239.x.x.x.

ipMRouteScopeNameAddressMask.name: ipMRouteScopeNameAddressMask
ipMRouteScopeNameAddressMask.description: The group address mask which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteScopeNameAddress identifies the group range associated with the multicast scope.

ipMRouteScopeNameLanguage.name: ipMRouteScopeNameLanguage
ipMRouteScopeNameLanguage.description: The RFC 1766-style language tag associated with the scope name.

ipMRouteScopeNameString.name: ipMRouteScopeNameString
ipMRouteScopeNameString.description: The textual name associated with the multicast scope. The value of this object should be suitable for displaying to end-users, such as when allocating a multicast address in this scope. When no name is specified, the default value of this object should be the string 239.x.x.x/y with x and y replaced appropriately to describe the address and mask length associated with the scope.

ipMRouteScopeNameDefault.name: ipMRouteScopeNameDefault
ipMRouteScopeNameDefault.description: If true, indicates a preference that the name in the following language should be used by applications if no name is available in a desired language.

ipMRouteScopeNameStatus.name: ipMRouteScopeNameStatus
ipMRouteScopeNameStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

ipMRouteMIBCompliance.name: ipMRouteMIBCompliance
ipMRouteMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the IP Multicast MIB.

ipMRouteMIBBasicGroup.name: ipMRouteMIBBasicGroup
ipMRouteMIBBasicGroup.description: A collection of objects to support basic management of IP Multicast routing.

ipMRouteMIBHopCountGroup.name: ipMRouteMIBHopCountGroup
ipMRouteMIBHopCountGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of the use of hop counts in IP Multicast routing.

ipMRouteMIBBoundaryGroup.name: ipMRouteMIBBoundaryGroup
ipMRouteMIBBoundaryGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of scoped multicast address boundaries.

ipMRouteMIBPktsOutGroup.name: ipMRouteMIBPktsOutGroup
ipMRouteMIBPktsOutGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of packet counters for each outgoing interface entry of a route.

ipMRouteMIBHCInterfaceGroup.name: ipMRouteMIBHCInterfaceGroup
ipMRouteMIBHCInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information specific to high speed (greater than 20,000,000 bits/second) network interfaces.

ipMRouteMIBRouteGroup.name: ipMRouteMIBRouteGroup
ipMRouteMIBRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information on the relationship between multicast routing information, and the IP Forwarding Table.

ipMRouteMIBPktsGroup.name: ipMRouteMIBPktsGroup
ipMRouteMIBPktsGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of packet counters for each forwarding entry.
